==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tremendous
<hw>Tre*men"dous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tremendus</ets> that is to be trembled at, fearful, fr.
<ets>tremere</ets> to tremble. See <er>Tremble</er>.]</ety> <def>Fitted
to excite fear or terror; such as may astonish or terrify by its
magnitude, force, or violence; terrible; dreadful; <as>as, a
<ex>tremendous</ex> wind; a <ex>tremendous</ex> shower; a
<ex>tremendous</ex> shock or fall.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>tremendous</qex> mischief was a foot.</q>
<rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Terrible; dreadful; frightful; terrific;
horrible; awful.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Tre*men"dous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Tre*men"dous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tremex</ent>⟦br⟧
